{"parse":{"title":"Meiping","pageid":32783755,"revid":823893595,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <i><b>meiping</b></i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Chinese_language\" title=\"Chinese language\">Chinese</a>&#58; <span lang=\"zh\">\u6885\u74f6</span>; <a href=\"/wiki/Pinyin\" title=\"Pinyin\">pinyin</a>&#58; <i><span lang=\"zh-Latn-pinyin\">m\u00e9ip\u00edng</span></i>; literally&#58; \"plum vase\", sometimes italicised in English)<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is a shape of vase in <a href=\"/wiki/Chinese_ceramics\" title=\"Chinese ceramics\">Chinese ceramics</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-welch17_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-welch17-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> It is traditionally used to display branches of <a href=\"/wiki/Plum_blossom\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Plum blossom\">plum blossoms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-welch17_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-welch17-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-slam_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-slam-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The meiping was first made of stoneware during the <a href=\"/wiki/Tang_dynasty\" title=\"Tang dynasty\">Tang dynasty</a> (618\u2013907).<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> It was originally used as a wine vessel, but since the <a href=\"/wiki/Song_dynasty\" title=\"Song dynasty\">Song dynasty</a> (960\u20131279) it also became popular as a plum vase and got its name \"meiping\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-guimet_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-guimet-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> It is tall, with a narrow base spreading gracefully into a wide body, followed by a sharply-rounded shoulder, a short and narrow neck, and a small opening.<sup id=\"cite_ref-slam_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-slam-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-guimet_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-guimet-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>They may have lids, and many lids have no doubt been lost. The equivalent shape in <a href=\"/wiki/Korean_ceramics\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Korean ceramics\">Korean ceramics</a>, where it was derived from Chinese examples, is called a <a href=\"/wiki/Maebyeong\" title=\"Maebyeong\">Maebyeong</a>. A distinct variant is the \"truncated meiping\", where there is only the top half of the usual shape, giving a squat vase with a wide bottom. This is largely restricted to <a href=\"/wiki/Cizhou_ware\" title=\"Cizhou ware\">Cizhou ware</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>   \n</p>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Porcelain_Vase.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Porcelain_Vase.jpg/107px-Porcelain_Vase.jpg\" width=\"107\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Porcelain_Vase.jpg/160px-Porcelain_Vase.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Porcelain_Vase.jpg/213px-Porcelain_Vase.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1192\" data-file-height=\"1341\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Cizhou_ware\" title=\"Cizhou ware\">Cizhou ware</a>, 13th century, <a href=\"/wiki/Song_dynasty\" title=\"Song dynasty\">Song dynasty</a>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Lidded_Prunus_Vase_(Meiping)_with_Lotus_Sprays_LACMA_AC1999.38.6.1-.2.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Lidded_Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Lotus_Sprays_LACMA_AC1999.38.6.1-.2.jpg/82px-Lidded_Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Lotus_Sprays_LACMA_AC1999.38.6.1-.2.jpg\" width=\"82\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Lidded_Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Lotus_Sprays_LACMA_AC1999.38.6.1-.2.jpg/123px-Lidded_Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Lotus_Sprays_LACMA_AC1999.38.6.1-.2.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Lidded_Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Lotus_Sprays_LACMA_AC1999.38.6.1-.2.jpg/164px-Lidded_Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Lotus_Sprays_LACMA_AC1999.38.6.1-.2.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1437\" data-file-height=\"2100\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Lidded vase with lotus sprays, <a href=\"/wiki/Qingbai_ware\" title=\"Qingbai ware\">Qingbai ware</a>, Southern Song period\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:%E8%80%80%E5%B7%9E%E7%AA%91%E9%9D%92%E9%87%89%E5%88%BB%E8%8A%B1%E7%89%A1%E4%B8%B9%E7%BA%B9%E6%A2%85%E7%93%B6.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/%E8%80%80%E5%B7%9E%E7%AA%91%E9%9D%92%E9%87%89%E5%88%BB%E8%8A%B1%E7%89%A1%E4%B8%B9%E7%BA%B9%E6%A2%85%E7%93%B6.JPG/80px-%E8%80%80%E5%B7%9E%E7%AA%91%E9%9D%92%E9%87%89%E5%88%BB%E8%8A%B1%E7%89%A1%E4%B8%B9%E7%BA%B9%E6%A2%85%E7%93%B6.JPG\" width=\"80\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/%E8%80%80%E5%B7%9E%E7%AA%91%E9%9D%92%E9%87%89%E5%88%BB%E8%8A%B1%E7%89%A1%E4%B8%B9%E7%BA%B9%E6%A2%85%E7%93%B6.JPG/120px-%E8%80%80%E5%B7%9E%E7%AA%91%E9%9D%92%E9%87%89%E5%88%BB%E8%8A%B1%E7%89%A1%E4%B8%B9%E7%BA%B9%E6%A2%85%E7%93%B6.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/%E8%80%80%E5%B7%9E%E7%AA%91%E9%9D%92%E9%87%89%E5%88%BB%E8%8A%B1%E7%89%A1%E4%B8%B9%E7%BA%B9%E6%A2%85%E7%93%B6.JPG/160px-%E8%80%80%E5%B7%9E%E7%AA%91%E9%9D%92%E9%87%89%E5%88%BB%E8%8A%B1%E7%89%A1%E4%B8%B9%E7%BA%B9%E6%A2%85%E7%93%B6.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"3456\" data-file-height=\"5184\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Yaozhou ware, <a href=\"/wiki/Celadon\" title=\"Celadon\">celadon</a>, Song dynasty\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Prunus_Vase_(Meiping)_with_Horizontal_Ribs_LACMA_AC1994.191.1.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Horizontal_Ribs_LACMA_AC1994.191.1.jpg/64px-Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Horizontal_Ribs_LACMA_AC1994.191.1.jpg\" width=\"64\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Horizontal_Ribs_LACMA_AC1994.191.1.jpg/96px-Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Horizontal_Ribs_LACMA_AC1994.191.1.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Horizontal_Ribs_LACMA_AC1994.191.1.jpg/128px-Prunus_Vase_%28Meiping%29_with_Horizontal_Ribs_LACMA_AC1994.191.1.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1075\" data-file-height=\"2018\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Vase with horizontal ribs, Southern Song period\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ming_Dynasty-Octagonal_Jar_(Meiping)_painted_in_copper-red_underglaze.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Ming_Dynasty-Octagonal_Jar_%28Meiping%29_painted_in_copper-red_underglaze.JPG/67px-Ming_Dynasty-Octagonal_Jar_%28Meiping%29_painted_in_copper-red_underglaze.JPG\" width=\"67\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Ming_Dynasty-Octagonal_Jar_%28Meiping%29_painted_in_copper-red_underglaze.JPG/101px-Ming_Dynasty-Octagonal_Jar_%28Meiping%29_painted_in_copper-red_underglaze.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Ming_Dynasty-Octagonal_Jar_%28Meiping%29_painted_in_copper-red_underglaze.JPG/135px-Ming_Dynasty-Octagonal_Jar_%28Meiping%29_painted_in_copper-red_underglaze.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"1836\" data-file-height=\"3262\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Vase with copper-red underglaze, <a href=\"/wiki/Ming_dynasty\" title=\"Ming dynasty\">Ming dynasty</a>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Vase_meiping_Mus%C3%A9e_Guimet_2418.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Vase_meiping_Mus%C3%A9e_Guimet_2418.jpg/90px-Vase_meiping_Mus%C3%A9e_Guimet_2418.jpg\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Vase_meiping_Mus%C3%A9e_Guimet_2418.jpg/135px-Vase_meiping_Mus%C3%A9e_Guimet_2418.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Vase_meiping_Mus%C3%A9e_Guimet_2418.jpg/180px-Vase_meiping_Mus%C3%A9e_Guimet_2418.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1488\" data-file-height=\"1984\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>18th-century vase\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:MET_DP251192.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/MET_DP251192.jpg/90px-MET_DP251192.jpg\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/MET_DP251192.jpg/135px-MET_DP251192.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/MET_DP251192.jpg/180px-MET_DP251192.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3001\" data-file-height=\"4000\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Porcelain, <a href=\"/wiki/Jingdezhen_ware\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jingdezhen ware\">Jingdezhen ware</a>, painted with cobalt blue under transparent glaze, 15th century\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Meiping&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">But not, for example, by the British Museum.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-welch17-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-welch17_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-welch17_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Welch, Patricia Bjaaland (2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=5sgO9BuZQSEC\"><i>Chinese art: a guide to motifs and visual imagery</i></a>. North Clarendon: Tuttle Publishing. p.&#160;17. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-8048-3864-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-8048-3864-1\">978-0-8048-3864-1</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=